Ovi saveti pomoći će vam da ostvarite sve što ste planirali u životu.
1. Cilj koji ste zacrtali mora biti nešto što iskreno želite.
2. Svoje ciljeve napišite razmišljajući pozitivno. Što ste pozitivniji u životu, više ćete pozitivnih rezultata ostvariti.
3. Budite precizni. Definišite datume, vreme, ali i parametre kojima ćete oceniti dostignuća.
4. Postavite prioritete. Ako se vaš cilj sastoji od nekoliko segmenita, definišite šta je prioritet.
5. Cilj ne sme da se sukobljava sa drugim ciljevima. 
6. Razradite i najsitnije detalje.
7. Birajte izazove. Cilj koji želite da ostvarite mora biti dovoljno visoko da vas motiviše, ali ne i previsoko, jer će vas to demotivisati.
8. Uvek zapisujte ono što želite da ostvarite.
Vizuelizacija uspeha važna je za ostvarivanje koliko i samo planiranje. #saveti #karijera #uspeh #career #advice #internetacademy

Great post taken from a running injury series by @optimize.yulia
・・・
Common running injuries series- Plantar fasciitis
🏃🏃🏃
The next few posts will concentrate on common (and sometimes less common) running injuries. I will attempt to structure it from the foot all the way up
🏃‍♀️🏃‍♀️🏃‍♀️
Our feet spend a lot of the day in a shoe where they are unable to splay out- placing the muscles in their shortened position for most of the day. Weak foot musculature can lead to a collapse through the arch, which puts the plantar fascia (the thick band of connective tissue on the bottom of the foot) under tension. Typical symptoms are pain on the bottom of the foot, especially in the first few steps of the morning, pain is worse when barefoot, and there is tenderness on the medial side of the heel
🏃🏃🏃
The plantar fascia extends from medial calcaneal tubercle to the base of the toes and functions to passively lock-up the foot, creating a natural rigid lever to push off of and propel the leg forward. When we extend our big toe during push off the plantar fascia tightens, lifting up the arch through a windlass mechanism
🏃‍♀️🏃‍♀️🏃‍♀️
When the muscles of our foot are unable to support the arch, the the plantar fascia becomes the only means of support for the arch and thus takes a further beating. This tension on the plantar fascia over time creates irritation and eventually pain. Running only exacerbates the issue as we require our feet to handle a lot more load and function at higher speeds
🏃🏃🏃
